 Four Nights with Anna. Ewa Mazierska addresses the main features of Skolimowski's films, such as their affinity to autobiographism and surrealism, while discussing their characters, narratives, visual style, soundtracks, and the uses of literature. She draws on a wide range of cinematic and literary texts, situating Skolimowski's work within the context of Polish and world cinema, and drawing parallels between his work and that of two directors, with whom he tends to be compared, Roman Polański and Jean-Luc Godard.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978184545807240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781845458072423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781845458072/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK